<Author>agent_bx
<Content>Tolerable Stayed here overnight while waiting to board a flight at Sydney Airport. Courtesy shuttle is very convenient, came promptly at the scheduled time from the airport. Bus driver provided a totally smiless service, and that pretty much summed up the service of the hotel. Upon entering hotel, the feeling was of a time warp back to the 80's. Hotel decor really needs some updating and has little style. The rooms were of an okay size, and we actually had a nice view of Sydney in the far distance. We used the gym facilities which were bare essential systems 10m on the outside of the hotel. We had trouble entering the gym, which was actually locked....but when we came back to reception, they just told us to swipe our card....which was not possible as that part of the hotel was actually locked by another member of the staff..... so we had to come back, and apparently another staff member locks the gate every shift but the others were not aware. The restaurant had surprisingly tasty food, although the environment was poor and banging in the kitchen could be hear loudly. Staff were friendly, but not well trained. This made the food overpriced. So overall it was a functional and convenient stay, but hardly a memorable experience, like using an old laptop with Windows 95 to type up an essay. 
