<Author>EuroFrequentFlyer
<Content>Not really impressed After an unimpressive experience at Holiday Inn Sydney Airport (the first room given smelled very strongly of urine, and the replacement room smelled musty and damp), I decided to try Mercure Hotel Sydney Airport. It appears that I have so far had no luck with finding a good Sydney Airport hotel (I was not particularly happy with Stamford Plaza either).One of the reception staff when I was checking in was not exactly terrific - not so much rude but told me that I had to have a printout of the confirmation email for my booking when there was no such requirement mentioned anywhere. It took a while to sort this out, but it was eventually agreed that I did not need to print it out and he begrudgingly allowed me to check into the room (for which I had already paid). It wasn't a very good start to the stay!The room was quite spacious, although quite dated. It smelled a little damp but nothing serious (I find that many Australian hotels smell damp for some reason). Bathroom cleanliness left a bit to be desired, and it also looked dated. Generally, the room was basic but adequate, although they could, and should, do better for the price they charge.The bar had a rather poor atmosphere (quite rough) and the service was very, very, very slow. It wasn't the fault of the staff - they appeared to be very short staffed, but from the customer's point of view it was quite unsatisfactory.Upon check-out, I noticed an error in the bill (someone else's food consumption was put on my room account) but the staff member (different one from the one that dealt with my check-in) dealt with it smoothly and without fuss, so that made up for the poor check-in experience.Hotel's transport to the airport worked very well - it was efficient and effective, so that's a good point.Overall, I was not very impressed with Mercure Sydney Airport. I'd stay there again if I need to, but I would much rather stay somewhere else - the only problem is that I have so far not found a decent alternative. 
