<Author>PLL-England
<Content>Not bad, but let down by noisy aircon in room Stayed here two nights prior to return flights back to England.This hotel is was not too bad. The room was large enough and clean enough. However, we had booked a King Bed and only got a Queen bed.The worst thing about the room was the noise of the air-conditioning unit - we didn't have ours turned on, but it kept clonking all the same. I complained the next morning just prior to going out for the day. Reception promised that it would be looked at. No surprise really when we got back to the room rather lat that night to find nothing done and the noise persisted. It was the most disturbed sleep I had during a three week stay in Australia. I don鈥檛 think customer satisfaction is top priority, probably because they know most stays are short term.The bar prices were average for hotel bars for Australia - about S$6 for a beer and A$3 for soft drink. The bar staff were friendly enough. Restaurant prices more expensive and I did not use the restaurant because of this, so cannot comment on the quality. The reception lobby is clean and pleasant enough.Booked online with popular web booking agent (who I used for other online bookings on the same holiday without problem, so know it was the hotel and not the online booking agent). However, on check-in the reception presented us with a balance due when it had already been paid. Luckily I had a copy of the online confirmation of payment/booking. The hotel made a photocopy of this and there were no further problems. However, it is still disconcerting when presented with a balance due (other hotels I stayed in on this same holiday, knew it had been paid up front on check-in). So holidaymakers beware, take a copy of your confirmation booking/payment with you.There is a shuttle bus from/to the airport, but it is not free and will cost A$5 per person per way. But this is convenient for getting to the hotel from the airport. The hotel is close by the airport.There is not a lot around the hotel, so do not expect bars or restaurants nearby. In the day you can walk along the Cook River as there is a small park facing the hotel. There is a free gym and free outdoor swimming pool at the hotel. Squash  Tennis courts could be hired if you are the sporty type 鈥?no sauna or Jacuzzi though.The cheapest way to get around from the hotel is by local train - a 15 minute walk to Wolli Creek station and it costs A$4.60 for a day ticket (trains run well past midnight). This is only one way to and then from Sydney city centre (any station ie. Central or Town Hall etc), but you can鈥檛 hop on hop off trains all day. But both Central  Town Hall are centrally located in Sydney. If you don鈥檛 mind catching the train then it is not hard to get to and from the city centre.If it wasn鈥檛 for the noisy air conditioning within then hotel, this would have been quite a decent hotel.P, England 
