<Content>try elsewhere We arrived around 9:00 p.m. and whilst in the lift I saw a poster advertising the hotel's tavern. The poster said the tavern was closed Sundays. Jokingly I said to my husband, Closed Sundays? What kind of a place is this?.In response, the businessman who was in the lift with us said, It's a bloody dreadful one and I wouldn't be here if I didn't have to. This turned out to be good advice.For example: As we were checking in, my husband went into the restaurant to see how late they served. He was told, 10:00. So we brought our bags to our room and came to the restaurant at 9:30. We were seated but told we should, and I quote, rush your order, as we are closing the kitchen and were hurried through the entire meal. We did not expect this sort of thing at an airport hotel (the meal was also lousy and expensive, which we DID expect at an airport hotel).The room was expensive, small, not cared for (e.g., light bulbs were burned out) and lacking in amenities.On the plus side, my husband said the gym was ok.We would not recommend this hotel. 
